
authserver:
	hyades-authserver
	kerberized netcat
	user certificate authority key
	authorized kerberoses
	keytab

server side:
	openssh
	hyades sshd_config
	user certificate authority pubkey
	signed ssh certificates

user side:
	openssh
	certificate authority validation
	req-cert


installation process for normal servers:
 * a script that can easily be downloaded
 * check the script's fingerprint
 * run it
 * contacts an admission server (?) to get keys signed
 * check the printed fingerprint against the admission script
 * script installs client CA things and sshd configuration


auth$ ./admit.sh <hostname> <secretdir>
(prints instructions for use! kinda...)
